:markdown
  You can specify a `controlsTpl` property to override the same property in a defined theme, by adding `controlsTpl` to your custom directive configuration:
pre.prettyprint
  = 'ng.module("xeditable").directive( "editableCustomDirective", function( editableDirectiveFactory ) {\n'
  = '     return editableDirectiveFactory({\n'
  = '        directiveName: \'editableCustomDirective\',\n'
  = '        ...\n'
  = '        controlsTpl: \'<div ng-class="{\\\'md-input-invalid\\\': $error}"></div>\',\n'
  = '        ...'